B Com in USA: Best Universities, Eligibility, Cost, Courses, Scholarships, Job

  • 544 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:May 01,2023 10:56 AM IST

The blog presented here talks about B.Com in USA. It also reasons out why a student should study the course in the USA. It also cites the basic eligibility, admission process, scholarships and available jobs after a B.Com in the USA.

The USA as a nation is one of the top-ranked when it comes to preference for international students for studies abroad in B.Com. Though US is expensive to study, it still offers many opportunities for these students in terms of top courses offered, best universities, job prospects and of course a growing economy.

As a B.Com student in USA, you will learn commerce, trade, economy, finance and other related subjects in details and gain knowledge as well become employable. Hence, pursuing a B.Com in USA will turn out to be a great choice for international students.  

This blog will now give details about everything you need to know for studying a B.Com in USA.

Reasons for Studying B.Com in USA

•USA is home to 17 out of top 50 universities in the world as per QS World Rankings. Therefore, the standard of education in these nations is among the best across the globe.
•The US economy is growing and there is high demand for professionals who are commerce graduates.
•The universities in US are home to some 1 million international students and provide a lively campus life and cultural diversity.
•The B.Com graduates are highly employable in USA and have great career opportunities.

B.Com in USA: Top Universities

Let’s first consider the best universities that offer a B.Com in the United States of America. The table below lists out these universities with some other details as well.

B.Com in USA: Eligibility

The basic eligibility criteria for seeking admission to a bachelor’s program in commerce in a US university is as follows:

•Successful completion of Class 12 or equivalent.
•Excellent academic credentials
•Proof of English language proficiency like IELTS scores of at least 6.0 or equivalent
•A personal statement
•Letters of Recommendations
•Good Interview Performance
•High quality portfolio

B.Com in USA: Admission Process

The admission process to be followed by an international student for seeking admission to a U.S. College or University is as follows:

•Write a personal statement stating the subject interest.
•Letter of Recommendation provided by a school teacher
•Apply online for admission on university or college website
•Complete any supplementary application questionnaire sent by the university or college
•Submit your academic transcripts
•Take a relevant test like SAT etc
•Take English language proficiency tests like IELTS etc

Which sectors employ a B.Com graduate in USA?

The following economic sectors employ a commerce graduate in the USA:

•Accounting
•Financial Services
•Tax Services
•Auditing
•Business Management
•Banking
•Warehousing etc.

B.Com in USA: Jobs Available

A commerce graduate can seek various job roles across various sectors of the economy. Some of these jobs have been listed below:

•Accounting Assistant
•Bookkeeper
•Accountant
•Logistics Manager
•Finance Manager
•Business Manager/Marketing Manager
•Finance/Business/Research Analyst

A B.Com graduate in USA, therefore, has vast opportunities available once they graduate with a qualification in commerce stream. The graduates are placed across sectors of the economy in highly paid job roles after doing B.Com in USA.

FAQ

Which country is best for a B.Com degree in the world?
B.Com can be pursued from a top university/college abroad. Universities or colleges abroad provide the best infrastructure and research facilities to international students. Top countries offering this course are USA, Canada, UK, Australia etc. but the courses here are highly expensive.
What is B. Com called in USA?
B.Com in USA is called Bachelor of commerce. It is also referred to as Bachelor of Science in Business Management, Bachelors in Business Management etc.
What can I do after a B.Com in the USA?
A commerce graduate can work as an Accountant, Account Assistant, Bookkeeper, Finance Manager, Operations Manager, Logistics Manager, Business Manager etc. across various sectors of economy.
Is B.Com a good degree?
Yes, it is indeed a good qualification. A commerce graduate can work across sectors of economy in various job roles. A commerce graduate can earn on average about 60,000 USD in the USA on annual basis.
Is mathematics compulsory for pursuing a B.Com degree?
Yes, universities keep mathematics as a subject a student needs to pass for a B.Com qualification. The student must be aware of basic mathematical operations and principles.
